<subSubSection pageId="78" pageNumber="79" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="78.[151,1437,387,774]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,531,557]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linne" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[625,762,531,557]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sylvaticus">
<emphasis box="[625,762,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">P. sylvaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[847,1040,531,558]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="323 - 351" refId="ref76025" refString="Shinohara, A. (1985 a) Web-spinning sawflies of the sylvaticus group of Pamphilius (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Systematic Entomology, 10, 323 - 351. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1985. tb 00141. x" type="journal article" year="1985">
Shinohara 1985 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1027,1040,531,558]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="307 - 320" refId="ref76348" refString="Shinohara, A. (1988 a) The group of Pamphilius sylvaticus (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae): Five new species and additional records from the Far East. Kontyu, Tokyo, 56, 307 - 320." type="journal article" year="1988">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 1988 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1109,1191,531,557]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="99 - 116" refId="ref76721" refString="Shinohara, A. (2001) The group of Pamphilius sylvaticus (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae): Two new species, new collection records, and a key to Palearctic species. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 7, 99 - 116." type="journal article" year="2001">a, 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1201,1276,531,557]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">2002b</bibRefCitation>
). From 
<collectingCountry box="[1361,1432,532,558]" name="South Korea" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Korea</collectingCountry>
, only a series of male specimens collected in 1992 and 1993 have been recorded (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1065,1245,567,593]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="99 - 116" refId="ref76721" refString="Shinohara, A. (2001) The group of Pamphilius sylvaticus (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae): Two new species, new collection records, and a key to Palearctic species. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 7, 99 - 116." type="journal article" year="2001">Shinohara 2001</bibRefCitation>
) and no material for molecular studies was available. The larvae are gregarious leaf rollers on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1014,1103,603,629]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Corylus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1014,1103,603,629]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Corylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="78.[151,1437,387,774]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
The maximum intraspecific 
<emphasis box="[519,533,640,665]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">p</emphasis>
-distance within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[722,822,639,665]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benesi">
<emphasis box="[722,822,639,665]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">P. benesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[892,956,640,666]" name="Japan" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Japan</collectingCountry>
was 2.2% in COI (n=7) and 0.6% in NaK (n=7) and the nearest neighbour was 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[577,696,675,701]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis box="[577,696,675,701]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">P. pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, diverging by a minimum of 2.9% in the COI analysis, and by a minimum of 0.5% in the NaK analysis. In both COI and NaK trees (
